page.title: 01AREA
page.content: The area being looked at lies on the outskirts of{Stockton}in the County of Cleveland in the North East of England. The housing consists of a {mixture}comprising the council estate of Roseworth, a small village of Thorpe Thewles with private housing and rural cottages, farm dwellings and large private houses. The latter border both sides of the main road called Junction Road which crosses part of the block and is a main artery to the neighbouring towns of Billingham and Norton. The{landscape}is mainly flat,there being few steep gradients and much of the{"BLOCK"}is in fact rural land used for agricultural purposes. At the moment this rural land seems in little danger of being developed, either for industrial,business or housing purposes.
